Modelesque Terms - NDAs or Non Disclosure Agreements
This applies to both Actors and Models
NDAs are legitimate contracts that should be taken seriously.
They are the only thing you should sign without first sending to your representation. 
You still send them a copy so they’re in the loop but you don’t necessarily need their approval or advice they way you should with contracts and releases.

Modelesque Term of the week : Walking lunch

Remember : Everything in the modeling industry is a case by case basis and that includes lunch

Some clients will provide a catered lunch and ask you your allergies. Some will not ask and you will need to speak up.

Some will give you a menu on set and you choose your order.

And some will give you a “walking lunch” where you are responsible for getting or brining your lunch. 
Some clients with reimburse you up to certain amount and some will not. 

If you are unsure ask your agent or the client.

#modelesque #modelesqueterms #lifeonset #modelonset #actingtips #actinglessons #acting101 #backgroundactors #standinactor #termsonset #setlifela #setlife🎬 #modelthings

Modelesque Term of the week 
Direct Booking

When a client books you without you, needing to come to a casting, or do a self tape

Of course, this would still include things like negotiating rates and usage.

It could also include a fitting.
If they call it a ‘fit to confirm’ it is not a ‘direct booking’ it is a ‘direct request’ and you are not booked and may not be booked depending onfitting. 

Should I explain more about ‘fit to confirm’ or ‘direct request’ ? 

Leave your requests for next weeks term in the comments 😁🥰

#modelesquemindset #modelesqueterms #modelesque #nativeearrings #beadedearrings #directbooking #modeleducation #acting101 #blueandbrown #brownandblue #workingmodels #lifeonset #actinglessons

Modelesque Term of the week - Advancement 
when you have completed a paid booking booked through your agency, but have yet to receive the payment, you can ask for an advancement.
This typically comes with an advancement fee.

You do not have to ask for advancements if you do not want them, and some agencies may say no to giving you them if they don’t have the money.

there is a law in California that says you are to be paid the day you work so I think the advancement fee is fraud, but most agencies will bully/gaslight you into thinking that there is nothing they can do to get you paid on time.
